Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: ntp-tools
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, bash (>= 4.0), python3
Recommends: openssl, dnsutils
Description: Complete NTP CLI: health check, sync monitoring, NTS and Roughtime
 ntp-tools provides a comprehensive set of NTP diagnostics from the
 command line.
 .
  - check: DNS resolution, port 123/UDP, offset, RTT, stratum, full details
  - monitor: live view of the local NTP daemon (chrony, ntpd, systemd-timesyncd)
  - diff: compare time offset between two servers or against the local clock
  - time: query current time from one or more NTP servers
  - NTS: TLS audit on port 4460, certificate validity, daemon capability
  - Roughtime: UDP query with Ed25519 signature verification, key via DNS TXT
